## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/regulatory-data.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Cross-check `Design.md` (Country & Layer Data) and `Logic.md` (map layer system, recommendations).

This rule applies to the **shared regulatory / tier datasets** (there is no separate `src/shared/policies/` folder in this repo). These two files are the canonical “policy” data for map layers and country copy.

## Human approval required

**Do not modify `layerData.ts` or `countryData.ts` without explicit human approval** — including: new layers, new tier keys, renamed `MapLayerOption` alignment, changed `CountryData` shape, bulk country additions/removals, or recommendation/spotlight logic that affects multiple screens.

After approval, update `/docs/features/regulatory-data.md` and any affected feature docs in the same change.

## Features that depend on this “policy system”

| Feature | Doc | Why it depends |
|---------|-----|----------------|
| World map | `/docs/features/world-map.md` | Choropleth tiers, colors, markers |
| ISP regulations panel | `/docs/features/isp-regulations-panel.md` | Spotlight, tiers, recommendations |
| Country detail view | `/docs/features/country-detail-view.md` | `getCountryData` copy and structure |
| Country browser | `/docs/features/country-browser.md` | Indirect (selection flows; layer alignment) |
| Map chrome | `/docs/features/map-chrome.md` | `MapLayerOption` must match layer keys |
| Application shell | `/docs/features/application-shell.md` | Global `selectedMapLayer` type |

## Reusable Components

Not applicable — data modules only. Consumers import functions/constants; do not duplicate tiers or country records in feature files.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- `MapLayerOption` in `RightVpnFeatures.tsx` must remain consistent with layer keys in `layerData.ts`.
- Tier union: `"high" | "medium" | "low"` (`LayerTier`) — changing enums requires full-app pass.

## Patterns to Follow

- Pure functions; no network I/O; extend via new exports and documented keys.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT fork tier or country data into feature components — always import from these modules.
- Do NOT change data shapes silently — update docs and all listed dependent features.
- Do NOT add routes.
